<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: TOPIC: LEVEL LIMIT +/- 4 (TXT)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Soul">Soul</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:38 a.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: TOPIC: LEVEL LIMIT +/- 4 (TXT)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=178" TARGET=_self>TOPIC: LEVEL LIMIT +/- 4 (TXT)</A> (Geiger)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Well, if we dont have time to implement a better system instead of the pk-switch till release, then why not simply make the +4/-4 difference in levels more flexible to protect newbies, but allow senior players a more interesting challenge of PvP combat.

<P>The difference in levels to allow combat could be as follows:
<BR>level 01 - 05 : -2 / +2
<BR>level 06 - 10 : -3 / +3
<BR>level 11 - 15 : -4 / +4
<BR>level 16 - 20 : -5 / +5
<BR>level 21 - 25 : -6 / +6
<BR>level 26 - 30 : -7 / +7
<BR>level 31 - 35 : -8 / +8
<BR>level 36 - 50 : -10 / +10
<BR>If two players of different level groups are trying to combat each other, the difference of the lower level player counts.
<BR>For exampel, a level 8 could not attack a level 5 because the limit of the level 5 is +2 / -2
<P>Another option:
<BR>Group against group or single player combat
<BR>For the purpose of combat possibility only it is wise to determine a group level.
<P>Exampel: A group of two level 19 and two level 15 players are ambushed by a group of two level 20 players.
<BR>Right now the level 15 players cant help their level 19 fellows. But with a group level, the four player group could become a level 17 group and would be able to defend theirselves against the level 20 group. This encourages group combat and protects any member of a group.
<BR>To prevent a level 30 player grouping with a level 1 player just to become a level 15 group, there should be flexible limitations like those used in the party exp. system.
<BR>So if there are too much level differences the lower players simply are of no importance to the group level.
<P>Please see this idea just as a short term solution till release date.
<BR>The ideas of TheRealmWeaver above are far better, but need more time to implement.
<P>Soul
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
