<TD COLSPAN=2><P><STRONG><font face=arial size=2>Message:</STRONG>
<BR><font face=arial size=2><TEXTAREA COLS=70 ROWS=15 NAME="body" WRAP=VIRTUAL>&gt; Well, if we dont have time to implement a better system instead 
&gt; of the pk-switch till release, then why not simply make the 
&gt; +4/-4 difference in levels more flexible to protect newbies, but 
&gt; allow senior players a more interesting challenge of PvP combat. 

&gt; The difference in levels to allow combat could be as follows: 
&gt; level 01 - 05 : -2 / +2 
&gt; level 06 - 10 : -3 / +3 
&gt; level 11 - 15 : -4 / +4 
&gt; level 16 - 20 : -5 / +5 
&gt; level 21 - 25 : -6 / +6 
&gt; level 26 - 30 : -7 / +7 
&gt; level 31 - 35 : -8 / +8 
&gt; level 36 - 50 : -10 / +10 
&gt; If two players of different level groups are trying to combat 
&gt; each other, the difference of the lower level player counts. 
&gt; For exampel, a level 8 could not attack a level 5 because the 
&gt; limit of the level 5 is +2 / -2 

&gt; Another option: 
&gt; Group against group or single player combat 
&gt; For the purpose of combat possibility only it is wise to 
&gt; determine a group level. 

&gt; Exampel: A group of two level 19 and two level 15 players are 
&gt; ambushed by a group of two level 20 players. 
&gt; Right now the level 15 players cant help their level 19 fellows. 
&gt; But with a group level, the four player group could become a 
&gt; level 17 group and would be able to defend theirselves against 
&gt; the level 20 group. This encourages group combat and protects 
&gt; any member of a group. 
&gt; To prevent a level 30 player grouping with a level 1 player just 
&gt; to become a level 15 group, there should be flexible limitations 
&gt; like those used in the party exp. system. 
&gt; So if there are too much level differences the lower players 
&gt; simply are of no importance to the group level. 

&gt; Please see this idea just as a short term solution till release 
&gt; date. 
&gt; The ideas of TheRealmWeaver above are far better, but need more 
&gt; time to implement. 

&gt; Soul 
